//! frffmpeg — fork/race/fold ffmpeg: the sovereign ffmpeg surface.
//!
//! Two directions over the same `ffmpeg` subprocess, with gnosis-frf doing the parallel
//! per-frame work:
//!
//! - **ENCODE** ([`generate`]): render procedural gnosis scenes in parallel (frf par-iter)
//!   and pipe RGB24 into ffmpeg for H.264. This is the original frffmpeg.
//! - **DECODE** ([`decode`]): pull RGB24 frames + presentation timestamps *out* of a video.
//!   This is the primitive third-eye's perception pipeline needs (the repo previously had
//!   no video decode anywhere — only encode).
//!
//! std-only, no C bindings: ffmpeg is driven as a subprocess, matching the existing sovereign
//! pattern (knot-viz-video, hello-holograph). Swap for `ffmpeg-next` later only if throughput
//! demands it.

